"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-07-29-paris-2024-dtigress-stun-australia-with-first-olympic-win-20-years\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  Nigeria's D'Tigress recorded a stunning 75-62 victory against world number three Australia in their opening fixture in the women's basketball event at the 2024 Olympic Games.  It was the D'Tigress's first win at the Olympics in 20 years.  Ezinne Kalu was Nigeria's top performer in the encounter, with 19 points, 5 rebounds, 5 assists and 3 steals  Rena Wakama's side trailed by eight points in the first quarter of the keenly contested game.  The Nigerians, however, rallied and led 41-28 at halftime.  Australia fought back and reduced the gap to just four points by the end of the third quarter.  D'Tigress stood up to the challenge and claimed a famous 75-62 victory at the end of the day.    Dozens arrested in France for planning disruptions at Olympics  Paris 2024 Olympic: Nigeria's D'Tigress makes history after winning first game  D'Tigress maintain 8th position in latest FIBA women's rankings  FIBA WWCQ: D'Tigress star Macaulay named in All-Star team  War: Australia confirms Iran strikes hit near airbase  D'Tigress captain Ogoke retires from national team  FG fulfils pledge to D'Tigress for winning 2025 FIBA Women's Afrobasket  Strait of Hormuz: We are not sending warships - Australia, Japan reply US President, Trump  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"